For example: if you want to “change” a font, color, size, location of assets/elements etc, I won’t charge you for that after the delivery of the 1st cut. However, if you want to “add” additional elements/content etc., I will bill for that time needed to incorporate the additional item(s) into the project. I do not charge for the actual stock footage, images, elements, or music used in your project (all copyright/royalty free) that I provide but will bill you for the time spent on searching for what you will ultimately approve.

My rate is $35/hr and it includes adding titles, lower 3rds, motion graphics/animation, SFX, color grading/correction, or audio mixing/enhancements. Of course this is just a baseline and there are many variables that will may make your project more or less expensive.

Let’s talk about it and fashion a realistic budget that works.

name: Guy P.
tagline: Full-stack Mobile & Web Development and UX Design
user_description:
I wake up everyday and eat mobile apps for breakfast and web apps for dinner! I genuinely love helping entrepreneurs and businesses build kick-ass software products to grow their businesses!

After a successful 10-year career building and launching consumer software products, I started the agency Valere Labs — a team of highly talented engineers, digital strategists, designers and QA engineers that are experts in:
✔ iPhone (Swift), Android (Kotlin & Java)
✔ React Native, Flutter
✔ AngularJS, ReactJS,
✔ Python, NodeJS, PHP, Django,, Laravel, Ruby on Rails, MongoDB.

Throughout my career I worked with five different software development agencies. Each agency had sub-par processes and lacked clear communication. Because I had launched several successful software products and observed issues from agencies and in-house software teams, I wanted to build the ultimate software agency that could create high performance web and mobile apps more efficiently and economically. So I did just that with Valere Labs...

High-level process building web and mobile apps at Valere Labs:
For each software project we go through a Discovery Phase with the client to get an in-depth understanding of the product we are building. We work with the client to develop low-fidelity mockups, flow diagrams, and rules to describe how the software will work. After the user experience is designed, we extract all of the individual “user stories” into a spreadsheet that describes every product use case. This process of identifying and articulating each “user story” meticulously ultimately ensures our vision for the application aligns with the clients before we write any code.

After the Discovery Phase, we enter the Build Phase. During this phase several Software Developers, a Project Manger, a UI Designer and our Quality Assurance team are assigned to your project. All members use the spreadsheet with “user stories” as a guide, knocking off each “user story” one-by-one.

The Project Manager articulates each “user story” to the Software Developer, and upon completion, the Quality Assurance team will then test that “user story” across several devices/browsers. Once all “user stories” are completed in a sprint/milestone, the client is able to test and provide feedback. We replicate this process for each sprint/milestone until the project is complete.

Within this high level process there are many sub-processes we perform to ensure success in terms of how we do research, review code, comment code, share updates with clients, etc. I believe our strong portfolio is a reflection of Valere Labs bullet proof software process.

Thanks for your interest in Valere Labs and reading this far :) Would love to learn about your project to see if we can be a good fit.

name: Jacob E.
tagline: INCREASE REVENUE without increasing ad spend
user_description:
INCREASE YOUR CONVERSIONS WITH A TRANSPARENT CRO STRATEGY & FRAMEWORK

*** Better Research = Better Strategy = More Leads = More Revenue ***

Have you been struggling to optimize your website for your goals? Maybe you want to increase your sales OR conversions but cannot *crack the code*. 

Through the framework I follow, I will help you identify the areas of improvement to start making more money and getting more customers with your website.

A bit about me: 

- Over 10 years of digital marketing experience
- Over 2 years of funnel optimization experience
- Satisfaction GUARANTEED 

Whether you need ;
- CRO (Conversion Rate Optimization)
- Landing Page Optimization
- Landing Page Building
- Email Marketing Optimization
- Traffic Optimization
- User Experience Research

A refined conversion framework can earn you more conversions & money within 24 hours!

Let me share with you the framework that I've been using successfully: 

Step 1: Observation (identifying where to focus by using analytics data)
Step 2: Research (identifying the 'why' behind user behavior by doing user surveys and sometimes interviews)
Step 3: Ideation (looking for ideas to solve the why through brainstorming and external research)
Step 4: Hypothesize (building a test hypothesis for the suggested optimization based on past testing benchmarks, industry benchmarks or experience)
Step 5: Roadmap (putting the optimization on the product/website roadmap)
Step 6: Wireframe (creating a wireframe for the idea)
Step 7: Design UI + Prototype (having a designer prepare a design based on the wireframe)
Step 8: Usability Test (Run the UI's in [login to view URL]. to identify usability issues)
Step 9: Value Test (live testing - a/b most often in google optimize OR other testing tool)
Step 10: Analyze ("this happened".."here is why".."moving forward"..)
Step 11: Spec + Documentation (full spec for engineers to implement sitewide the "winner" of the experiment, if there is one)
Step 12: Release (the optimization is released to the wild)
Step 13: Usability test (again)
Step 14: Evangelize (make sure the internal team knows about the optimization)
Step 15: Re-Analyze ("this happened".."here is why".."moving forward"..)
Step 16: Re-start from step 1

Generally speaking, I like to work based on this schedule (more or less).

Week 1 - Complete steps 1-6
Week 2 - Complete steps 7 & 8
Week 3/4 - Complete step 9
Week 5 - Complete steps 10 & 11
Week 6 - Complete steps 12-14
Week 7/8 - Complete step 15 less

So what do you say? Let's have a chat?

name: Justin S.
tagline: Full Stack Engineer focused on web services.
user_description:
Hi, I'm Justin,

I'm a software engineer who at the moment specializes in web development, whether it's building an interactive user interface, writing the server application and APIs that make it run. I've spent the last decade working with startups and small businesses building websites and business applications.

I recently decided to bring my experience into the startup community as well. I began my professional career as a software developer but I've spent these years also learning a great deal about business, sales, and web design, and would like to bring all that I've learned out there to help you while I build my new business as a full-time freelance web developer.

I joined Bombfell, an online personal styling service for men, as the first full-stack engineer working side-by-side with the CTO. At that time the company was no more than the founders and a handful of stylists working together out of a small apartment. Starting with an AWS hosted python server, a MySQL database, and a front-end built on AngularJS which we later changed to React.js, over the next six years we continuously built and upgraded the public website, internal portals for stylists to shop and communicate with customers, as well as integrated billing, shipping, and inventory management systems. Together, we acquired series A funding and expanded our technical team from the CTO and I to a team of full-stack engineers, designers, and data scientists. As our team grew I learned more about the responsibilities necessary in leading project development as well as the tools that could be used to streamline development and testing processes. By the time I left, Bombfell had grown to include hundreds of stylists nationwide with a large number of devoted customers.

More recently, I served as the first and lead engineer at the recently-founded MeetGerry, which aims to pair individuals seeking long-term residential care with their ideal care facilities. Here, I took over the reigns from an outsourced development crew that had created a small public website built with an out-of-date version of Ruby on Rails hosted on servers outside of our control. My first step was to re-implement the website with an identical but more functional python Pyramid server on AWS with a postgresql database. Using React.js for the front-end and more mobile friendly CSS, I expanded the existing site and added an easily customized sign-up system for new clients in addition to creating an internal portal to assist in marketing and customer development. With automated development and testing processes in hand, I brought onboard a data scientist, designer, and another full-stack engineer to continue to grow MeetGerry and later pivot into the next iteration of the company, GerryCare.

Thank you for your time in reading this and all the best,

- Justin Sousa

name: Ash T.
user_description:
Ash Tankha has more than 30 years experience in patent drafting, patent (prior art) search, patent filing, patent infringement, and patent prosecution matters. Representative patent applications, both pending and granted, are listed in the following link: [login to view URL]

Ash is a partner at Lipton, Weinberger & Husick. Ash has significant experience in trademark filing and trademark prosecution. Drafted and filed more than 700 patent applications and more than 500 trademark applications. He has obtained about 500 patents for my clients.

Ash Tankha has filed patent applications in different domains such as software, business methods, mechanical, electronic communication and semiconductors, chemical, pharmaceutical and biotechnology with the US Patent and Trademark Office and other foreign patent offices (through foreign associates). You may contact Ash for references.

Prior to filing a patent application, an extensive prior art search is conducted over various databases to determine if the concept of the invention is novel. The patent application is consequently filed with the US patent office after the client has approved of the same.

If the search result indicates that the inventive concept is novel and may contain patentable subject matter, a draft of the patent application is prepared for filing with the U.S.PTO. 

Once the draft of the patent application is prepared, the draft of the application is sent to the client for the client's review and comments. Once the application is approved by the client for filing, the patent application is filed with the U.S.PTO or the appropriate foreign patent office.

Ash files responses to office actions issued by the U.S.PTO for patent applications under examination. Often, inventors receive an office action, for example an objection or rejection of a claim from the US Patent and Trademark Office, for which the patent attorney prepares the responses and optionally interviews the U.S.PTO patent examiners to advance the prosecution of the application.

Ash provides services for clients both nationally and internationally in patent related matters in diverse areas of technology. 

For patent or trademark inquiries, please call: Ash Tankha, Patent Attorney, Lipton, Weinberger & Husick.

name: Sumante H.
user_description:
As Sumante J Hutchinson aka God Sent Genius™ has evolved as an artist, producer, and entrepreneur, so has his approach creatively and as an entertainment business person. An elusive, enigmatic, talented, and focused individual, GSG™ is the Chief Executive Officer and full shareholder of the San Francisco Bay Area recording company "Phantom LS Records LLC". He founded the company in April 2017 and is forming other companies on the side as he works on building his own label. Under the company, he retains his rights to all of his creative works through his direct deals with BMI, Soundexchange, and Sentric Music (Ingrooves), which he signed in 2015. Through his connection base and research while attending Diablo Valley College, San Ramon and The University of California, Santa Cruz, God Sent Genius™ has carried a formidable network and has challenged the status quo year after year.

He began his journey and business building in 2011 at the age of 17 when he started a non profit media group called, "No Established Culture™", in Rocklin, CA. At the age of 18, he chose the name "God Sent Genius™" because faith is very important to him and he believes his talent is God given. In April 2014, he began networking with the staff of Universal Music Group, Def Jam, G.O.O.D. Music, and Roc Nation to learn Music Business while studying marketing/promotions with their A&R/Press Teams at Starlight PR. He retained his master use rights after his first single was released and has complete control over his company. Today, he keeps a rolodex of many influential contacts within the entertainment industry.

In September 2016, after a range of live performances at venues such as The House of Blues, Venue Oakland, Rain Nightclub, Blue Lamp Nightclub, The Dragonfly, and The New Parish, while releasing several now accessible mixtape releases, GSG™ began working on patenting a software/hardware design that is still a work in progress, Crowdsurf.Live™. He transferred to The University of California, Santa Cruz in 2018 and has remained focused on the success of the companies and all parties involved ever since. In the summer of 2021, GSG™️ contracted with BeatStars & Sony Music Publishing for the purpose of growing his business and establishing a solid presence within the Music Industry as both a producer and artist.

God Sent Genius™️ is also a donor and former volunteer for UNA-USA, a philanthropic non profit organization related to the United Nations, which he assisted for three and a half years with Sustainability Investment and Philanthropy. He has experience as a Marketing / Sales expert that he carries from his tenures with Express, Alliance Marketing Services, and Cadillac. Aside from Media and Entertainment, his interests include environmental preservation and climate change mitigation.

Michael Birchfield grew up in Alabama with his 4 younger siblings, mother and father. Michael lives in Birmingham, Alabama with his wife and two cats. Michael received a collegiate Tennis scholarship at Central Alabama Community College and attended there from 2007 to 2009 studying computer science. Michael's love for music led him to begin his audio and video production career, which took him away from college in 2009. He worked and traveled with several bands as a jack-of-all-trades, managing events, running sound boards, and mastering, recording and editing video and audio content. name: Tracy C.
tagline: Producer, Musician, Singer Arranger Mix Engineer
user_description:
Tracy Carter: Producer. Musician. Artist. Philanthropist. 

Mr. Tracy Carter is a gifted and talented producer, songwriter keyboardist, Music Director, vocalist, percussionist, and philanthropist. 

Born and raised in Sacramento, California, Tracy began playing the piano at the age of nine. With a combination of hands-on experience, formal education and mentoring, Tracy developed his talent, skills, and passion into a brand and musical style that is unique and captivating. With influences such as Stevie Wonder, Quincy Jones, Herbie Hancock, Chick Corea and much more, Tracy has inspirations and aspirations to musically achieve and excel on various levels of the industry. In 1996, Tracy relocated to Los Angeles, CA to begin a career as a professional musician and recording artist. He was the head musician / MD at Faith Central Bible Church for 22 years. Tracy has toured as a Music Director, keyboardist and/or vocalist for the following; Chaka Khan, Gerald Albright, Dave Koz, Euge Groove, just to name a few. He performed in the capacity of Music Director for Gerald Albright, for nine years. 

In addition to performing and touring Tracy has recorded on multiple CD projects for Grammy-nominated artists. He also wrote and co-produced the songs “Better Day,” “The Time is Here,” and “Sunday’s Best” on two of the late Wayman Tisdale’s CDs. After producing successful projects for multiple musicians of various genres, Tracy began to focus his energy on completing a product of his own. Tray continued to develop a signature style that produces a crisp and unique sound with a seasoned blend of musical flavor that creates a solid fan base to listeners and other musicians. His musical creations are extremely captivating and sought by many of the industry greats. 

Tracy released his debut smooth jazz CD titled “Dimensions of a Musician” in 2015. This CD showcased his multilevel facets as a songwriter, musician, lyricist, vocalist, producer, and entrepreneur. The CD garnered rave reviews and was both critically and commercially successful. The Dimensions CD features Wayman Tisdale, Gerald Albright, Donald Hayes, Melvin Lee Davis, And Andre Delano/Tracy’s has also released a Christian project called, "My Confidence" with a blend of jazz and soulful gospel that relays meaningful messages that relating to current circumstances. Both CD’s were written and produced by Tracy and released on his own record label, Eternal Sound Music Group (ESMG), LLC, that he created in 2008.

Once you have been captivated with his performance, you are sure to be amazed by the multiple levels of elevation that he exudes through his powerful collection of music and talent.

Lee's credentials include being the VP of two top-tier Marketing / PR firms in Miami; serving as the Editor / Publisher of an award-winning, four-color City Magazine; and being the founding Editor / Publisher of a six-state, regional, Industry newspaper, owned by a New York-based publisher which produced 22 monthly business / industry magazines and staged business / industry Trade Shows.

name: Crystal G.
user_description:
Crystal has over 15 years of proven ability to lead and manage projects to improve performance and operational efficiencies. She is excellent in developing project plans, providing consulting services, process improvement, training and management support. She is a hands-on leader and proficient in identifying the direction of technology and its application to business systems.

Crystal has earned a Master of Library Science from Texas Woman’s University, and a Master of Science in Technology Project Management from the University of Houston. As a Project Management Professional® (PMP), she is focused on carefully assessing organizations and finding new ways to improve operations and highlighting key project inter-dependencies and align releases across interdependent projects. 

Crystal enlisted in the United States Army in June 2006. After completing training as an Information Technology Specialist (25B), she was stationed at US Army Garrison-Humphreys, located near Anjeong-ri and Pyeongtaek metropolitan areas in South Korea where her project management experience began. Crystal went on to receive her commission in 2010 as a graduate of the historical United States Army's Officer Candidate School located at Fort Benning, Georgia. Crystal currently holds the rank of Captain in the Inactive Ready Reserve (IRR). 

Crystal uses her diverse industry insights, technical and presentation skills to obtain funding and successfully executed office renovations at the Metropolitan Transit Authority of Harris County (Houston Metro) headquarters building. This project, requested by prominent Metro board member Lex Frieden, impacted over 200 employee’s and highlighted Crystal’s ability to manage a tightly funded project from conceptualization to reality. With her focus on automation and innovation, her platform is developing and maturing an organizational processes to support the effective management of projects.

Recent Accomplishment: In an effort to improve and automate data capture, Crystal designed and configured the first Lessons Learned Knowledge Center for Boeing’s VC25A Program, (Air Force One) using the SharePoint platform. The VC25A Lessons Learned system is a database of lessons learned from contributors across the program and supports cost and schedule improvement goals. With a background in information technology, military logistics, public transportation and aviation, Crystal demonstrates skilled use of project management tools, techniques and methods to deliver results that exceed expectations.

Crystal is a member of Project Management Institute, the world's leading association for those who consider project, program, or portfolio management their profession; and upholds the Institute's Code of Ethics and Professional Conduct.

PMP®: Project Management Professional
Credential # 1907527
Renews: 24 January 2025

name: Clark G.
user_description:
Greetings, from Grand Rapids, Michigan, USA.

I look forward to applying my thirty-seven years of experience in proofreading, editing, copy editing, and writing to your Very Important Project (VIP).

I have a wide range of interests, including philosophy and the arts; history and social sciences; mathematics, technology and engineering; and medicine, biology, genetics, and other life sciences. I am also a voracious reader of sci-fi, fantasy, adventure, and all things Stephen King. I enjoy poetry and biographical works as well, and I am a serious reader of the King James Bible.

I am studious, knowledgeable, and have an expansive vocabulary, all traits of critical importance when the outcome of your VIP is on the line. Whether the subject is literary in nature, academic, technical, or business-oriented, I guarantee a working comprehension of your needs (or the ability to become versed in a matter of moments). Moreover, I promise to meet (or even exceed!) your expectations with regard to communication, and the successful completion of your VIP is a forgone conclusion – "a result that can be predicted with certainty."

Born and raised in the American Midwest, my native language is American English (AE). I am also quite fluent in British English (BE). In AE, my proficiency is of the highest level. Idioms, slang, and even most local variations come naturally to me.

I believe my greatest strengths as an editor are my attention to detail; my ability to discern your meaning and help you find a better (clearer, more concise, and therefore more dynamic) way to say it; and my ability to correctly employ grammar, spelling, and punctuation. I enjoy "wordsmithing," sentence structure, and compositional editing, I excel at the intricacies of punctuation, and I thoroughly understand the rules of spelling and capitalization. I am ruthless on typos, and errors of all kinds virtually throw themselves at my feet. The grammatically incorrect know me only as ... Nemesis.

Having said that, I respectfully honor poetic license, and the author's voice always reigns supreme in the VIPs in my care. The customer's vision is at the forefront of my mind. If you need a piece thoroughly vetted, reviewed with a fine-tooth comb, edited or rewritten with precision – if you need a job done correctly, especially to a certain specification – I am the freelancer you're looking for.

Thank you for your consideration. I hope to meet you soon.

OUR BRAND

Reverse Fall LLC is a Philadelphia-based design and development agency founded on the philosophy of 'Natural Design', where interacting with our software is natural to our end-users and understanding our designs feels second-nature. 


GIVING BACK

We believe that technology should be connected to the world around us, not the other way around, and are committed to environmentally sustainable business practices. As part of this commitment, we donate 10% of all profits to environmental sustainability projects relating to green energy and sustainable agriculture solutions. We believe that by doing our part, we can set an example for other businesses and encourage a trend toward giving back to the world while continuing to innovate through technology.


OUR WORK

Due to the nature of design and development, we have had the opportunity to work on a wide variety of projects for customers across the United States. As of 2020, we have designed:
- 47 websites spanning 28 different industries;
-181 logos;
- 200+ print projects;
- 6 full-time digital advertising contracts.


WHY WORK WITH US

We know what it's like to dive into a new project and get overwhelmed with all the intricacies that may arise. At the heart of our business model is the idea that design is a collaborative process where our job is to work WITH you, not just FOR you. Although slightly untraditional in the industry, we make a point of keeping our client's up-to-date on each step of the process. This includes upfront menu pricing**, a dedicated "project tracker" to view the current status of your project, and an "instant feedback" panel to keep communication open throughout the project lifecycle.

name: Prince Evans G.
user_description:
Teamwork: Teamwork requires adaptation, open-mindedness, and task orientation. Network administrators collaborate fellow technology professionals and other colleagues to identify a common need and work toward it together. As part of a team, network administrators need interpersonal skills to listen and be receptive to ideas and suggestions.
Communication: Verbal and written communication skills are essential for network administrators. As individuals who install and oversee complex technological networks, network administrators must explain concepts and use to others. Network administrators need to be clear, concise, and respectful as they interact with peers and colleagues.
Critical Thinking: Critical thinking involves analysis, interpretation, and evaluation of evidence with an open mind. It also enables individuals to explain topics and issues objectively. By thinking through problems, concerns, and suggestions critically, network administrators solve problems and make rational, well-informed decisions.
System Administration: Network administrators must understand the nuances of all kinds of software and operating systems to troubleshoot and maintain the systems used within an organization. System administration entails managing these software systems and making sure various systems, software, hardware, and other technologies work efficiently and remain current.
Network Support: Networks within a business or organization generally include internet- and web-based operating systems, and network administrators make sure that these systems work properly. Network support involves helping users troubleshoot connectivity issues and assist in setup processes.
